PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/02/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(88)90028-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199688900281
AB  - Sufficient conditions are given for any tariff or quota to be protective under uncertainty, where assets are not traded internationally, and commodities are traded. It is shown that if both goods are normal goods, then any small tariff or quota is protective, even if it varies with the random state of nature. A sufficient condition is also given for large trade restrictions to be protective under uncertainty. These results thus generalize those of Helpman and Razin, who showed that when both goods are normal goods, a small ad valorem tariff which is independent of the state of nature is protective.
ER  - 

